.TH VALKEY-SERVER 1 "2024"
.SH NAME
valkey-server \- Persistent key-value database server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B valkey-server
.RI [ configfile ]
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Valkey is a high-performance, open-source key-value data store and data
structures server. Keys can contain strings, hashes, lists, sets, sorted sets,
bitmaps, hyperloglogs, geospatial indexes, and streams.
.PP
Valkey is a community-driven fork of Redis, licensed under the BSD 3-Clause
license.
.SH OPTIONS
.IP "configfile"
Read configuration from the specified file.
Default configuration file is \fB/etc/valkey/valkey.conf\fP.
.IP "\-\-port PORT"
Listen on the specified port (default: 6379).
.IP "\-\-daemonize yes|no"
Run as a daemon (default: no; managed via systemd in this package).
.SH NOTES
On Debian and Ubuntu systems,
.B valkey-server
is managed by
.BR systemd (1).
The service unit is installed as \fBvalkey-server.service\fP but is
.B not enabled or started
automatically. Use
.BR systemctl (1)
to manage it:
.PP
.RS
.nf
systemctl enable valkey-server.service
systemctl start  valkey-server.service
.fi
.RE
.PP
Multiple independent instances can be started with the template unit:
.B valkey-server@<name>.service
each using \fB/etc/valkey/valkey\-<name>.conf\fP as its configuration file.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/valkey/valkey.conf
Default server configuration file.
.TP
.I /var/lib/valkey/
Data directory (RDB snapshots, AOF files).
.TP
.I /var/log/valkey/
Log directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR valkey-cli (1),
.BR valkey-sentinel (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Maintained by community-pkgs <https://github.com/community-pkgs/packages> for the Debian/Ubuntu packages.
.PP
Valkey was created by the Valkey contributors. See https://valkey.io for details.
